Homepage: https://github.com/bobbycomet/XKM-Multi-Kernel-Manager
Description: Multi-Kernel Manager for XanMod, Liquorix, and mainline kernels
 XKM is a PyQt6 GUI for installing, removing, holding/unholding, and
 keeping track of XanMod, Liquorix, and mainline Ubuntu kernel packages.
 .
 It handles apt repository setup for XanMod and Liquorix, apt-mark
 hold/unhold, a GRUB update safety net after install/remove, and DKMS
 module rebuilds for newly installed kernels, with a reboot prompt once
 everything is ready.
 .
 All privileged operations (package install/remove, hold/unhold, adding
 repositories, updating GRUB, DKMS rebuilds, and rebooting) are performed
 by a small dedicated helper script authorized via a scoped polkit policy,
 rather than granting the whole application broad root privileges.
